<br>
And how does Verant not advancing the plot prevent us, the players, from using the existing plot to generate our backstories?  Back in my dark elf days, there was someone who created a massive story about being the bastard child of Innorruk.  And then Lanys T'Val showed up, which kinda made things difficult.  Yes, I know that Everquest is a fairly static world; I'm not arguing that one way or another.  But the fact that is IS static, that the storyline IS in place, and that only occasionally are things going to happen which completely screw over the stories we're trying to tell, in my mind, isn't always a bad thing...<br>
<br>
I guess I feel like there's this complaint I don't understand, and when you respond this way, you're agreeing that it's there, but you're not helping me understand why that prevents the PLAYERS from taking advantage of what's available...<br>
